    "ScalingProfile": {
      "description": "Scaling configuration for a model deployment. Exactly one of `manual` or\n`autoscale` must be set.\n\nThis mutual-exclusion constraint is enforced by the service at request\nvalidation time, not by the schema. A PUT request that sets both `manual`\nand `autoscale`, or sets neither, is rejected with HTTP 400 (Bad Request)\nand an `InvalidScalingProfile` error code;\n\nScale-to-zero semantics differ between the two modes:\n- `manual` permits `replicas: 0`. This is an explicit operator action to\n  stop serving traffic while keeping the `ModelDeployment` resource (and\n  its configuration) in place. While at zero replicas the endpoint\n  returns errors for inference requests, and the deployment releases its\n  GPU capacity.\n- `autoscale` does not permit `minReplicas: 0`. Autoscaling decisions are\n  driven by serving-server runtime metrics (request rate, queue depth,\n  GPU utilization); at zero replicas there is no signal for the\n  autoscaler to scale back up from. Combined with GPU cold-start time\n  (on the order of minutes) and constrained regional GPU capacity, a\n  scale-from-zero event would produce unacceptable first-request latency\n  and a high risk of capacity unavailability. Callers that want\n  autoscaling with an idle state should delete the `ModelDeployment`\n  instead.",
      "properties": {
        "autoscale": {
          "description": "Autoscaling configuration. Mutually exclusive with `manual`.",
          "oneOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/AutoscaleProfile"
            },
            {
              "$ref": "https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/common/definitions.json#/definitions/expression"
            }
          ]
        },
        "manual": {
          "description": "Manual scaling configuration with a fixed replica count. Mutually exclusive with `autoscale`.",
          "oneOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/ManualScalingProfile"
            },
            {
              "$ref": "https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/common/definitions.json#/definitions/expression"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "type": "object"
    },
